title: Fulham v Tottenham Hotspur: match preview | Football
text:
Fulham, resurgent just outside the play-off positions in the Championship, have beaten Premier League opposition twice this term having seen off Middlesbrough in the EFL Cup and Hull in this competition. Slavisa Jokanovic will hope to make that a hat-trick against a stuttering Tottenham Hotspur . Mauricio Pochettino intends to make changes at Craven Cottage in the hope the fringe players offer some freshness. Spurs have won on their last three trips across the capital, and none of the side who lost 4-0 on their last FA Cup visit here, six years ago, remain at the club. Dominic Fifield 
Kick-off Sunday 2pm
